adjectives.description: unterrific (comparative more unterrific, superlative most unterrific)

entries.meaning: Unterrifying; not causing or involving terror.

examples: Of these the nearest — yet about twelve miles distant — is the before-named Brezon, a majestic, but unterrific, fortalice of cliff, forest, and meadow, with unseen nests of village, and unexpected balm and honey of garden and orchard nursed in its recesses.
